main event: A possible satellite sighting was reported in the Pacific Ocean on October 1, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by the military, indicating it was likely a formal UFO report.
The object was observed for a reported time, suggesting it was not a typical satellite pass.
The location was in the Pacific Ocean at coordinates 43-00'N 173-00'W.
The object was described as having a brightness magnitude of a first star, which is unusual for a satellite.
The report concludes that the object was likely a USAF IT CPO II satellite, but notes that no unusual phenomena were observed.
